(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:13.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:~&amp;#34;ＭＳ ゴシック~&amp;#34;;mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;mso-bidi-font-style:italic&amp;#34; %)**Attempts to manage the world render Earth and its inhabitants as objects, awaiting the subjective United States’ federal government’s action.  This form of dualism renders everything a self-circulating resource at humanity’s disposal, revealing one way of better relating to the world, all the while eclipsing other modes of thought.**

